        <div class="content">

            <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
                 TOPIC 1 — TWO POINTERS
            ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
            <div class="topic-card" id="tp1">
                <div class="topic-header">
                    <div class="topic-num">01</div>
                    <div style="flex:1">
                        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap">
                            <div class="topic-title">Two Pointers</div>
                            <span class="tier-badge tier-T1">Foundation</span>
                            <span class="topic-type">Technique</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="topic-meta">54 problems · sorted array, linked list, string</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-body">
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Tests ability to eliminate search space using invariants. O(n) solutions to O(n²) problems demonstrate insight, not brute force.</div>
                    <div class="core-box"><strong>Core Idea:</strong> Maintain lo/hi (or slow/fast) pointers. Decide which to move based on a monotone condition. The invariant — what you prove about the space between pointers — IS the algorithm.</div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Sub-Variants</div>
                    <div class="pill-grid">
                        <span class="pill">Opposite-end sorted</span><span class="pill">Opposite-end maximize</span><span class="pill">Opposite-end count</span><span class="pill">Three-pointer (3Sum)</span><span class="pill">Four-pointer (4Sum)</span><span class="pill">Dutch National Flag</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — cycle detection</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — cycle entry</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — middle finding</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — kth from end</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — palindrome</span><span class="pill">Fast/slow — implicit graph</span><span class="pill">Two pointers on two arrays</span><span class="pill">String two-pointer</span><span class="pill">Fill from ends</span><span class="pill">Two-pointer + sorting</span><span class="pill">Greedy + opposite-end</span><span class="pill">Multi-pointer + heap</span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Problem Set</div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
