                        <tr><td class="num-cell">20</td><td><span class="l4">Hard</span></td><td><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/substring-with-largest-variance/" target="_blank">LC 2272</a></td><td class="prob-name">Substring With Largest Variance</td><td><span class="diff-h">Hard</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Kadane's on character frequency differences</td><td class="insight">For each (a,b) pair: +1 for a, −1 for b; Kadane's with "≥1 b seen" guard; Hard: O(26²) pairs × state dimension</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">21</td><td><span class="l4">Hard</span></td><td><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/constrained-subsequence-sum/" target="_blank">LC 1425</a></td><td class="prob-name">Constrained Subsequence Sum</td><td><span class="diff-h">Hard</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Kadane's + deque (gap ≤ k)</td><td class="insight">dp[i] = nums[i] + max(0, windowMax); Hard: gap-constrained subsequence → sliding-window-max DP, not O(nk)</td></tr>
