                    <div class="sec-title">Custom Problem Statements</div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>🔧 #9 — Minimum Sum Subarray:</strong> Given integer array nums, find the minimum sum of any non-empty contiguous subarray. Constraints: 1 ≤ n ≤ 10⁵, −10⁴ ≤ nums[i] ≤ 10⁴. Example: [2,−3,4,−1,−2] → −3. Key Insight: Replace max with min in every comparison; init minEndingHere = nums[0]; start loop at index 1.</div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>🔧 #10 — Max Subarray Sum with Length ≥ K:</strong> Find max sum of any contiguous subarray of length ≥ k. Constraints: 1 ≤ k ≤ n ≤ 10⁵, −10⁴ ≤ nums[i] ≤ 10⁴. Example: n=6, k=3, [1,−1,2,3,−2,4] → 7 ([2,3,−2,4]). Key Insight: prefix[i] − min(prefix[0..i−k]); track rolling minimum of prefix sums as i advances.</div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>🔧 #23 — Max Subarray Sum Divisible by K:</strong> Find max sum of non-empty contiguous subarray whose sum % k == 0. Constraints: 1 ≤ n ≤ 10⁵, 1 ≤ k ≤ 100. Example: n=5, k=3, [2,7,−4,3,2] → 9 ([2,7]). Key Insight: HashMap of remainder → earliest prefix index; prefix[j]−prefix[i] with same mod gives the largest valid subarray.</div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Pattern Recognition Triggers</div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
                        <thead><tr><th>Trigger Phrase</th><th>Sub-Variant</th><th>When It BREAKS</th></tr></thead>
                        <tbody>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Find maximum/minimum sum of contiguous subarray"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Standard Kadane's; single pass, two variables</td><td class="trigger-breaks">Never breaks for plain max/min sum</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"...in a circular array / array can wrap around"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Circular: max(normalMax, total − minSubarray)</td><td class="trigger-breaks">All-negative: circular gives 0 (empty) → fall back to normalMax</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Maximum product of contiguous subarray"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Track both maxProd AND minProd</td><td class="trigger-breaks">Zeros reset both; treat zeros as natural reset points</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Maximum sum path through any node in a binary tree"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Tree Kadane's (DFS post-order)</td><td class="trigger-breaks">Can't return both branches to parent — return only one branch upward</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"You can delete at most one element / skip one"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Two-state DP: withDeletion + withoutDeletion</td><td class="trigger-breaks">More than one deletion → generalised deletion-count DP state</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Max sum of exactly/at least/at most K length subarray"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Kadane's + prefix sums with rolling minimum</td><td class="trigger-breaks">Exact length K only → fixed sliding window, not Kadane's</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Substring with largest variance / frequency difference"</td><td class="trigger-variant">26² pair Kadane's; map char → +1/−1</td><td class="trigger-breaks">More than two types still requires pair enumeration</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="trigger-phrase">"Max score jumping with gap limit k"</td><td class="trigger-variant">Kadane's DP + monotonic deque for sliding-window max</td><td class="trigger-breaks">No gap limit → plain DP or greedy</td></tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>

                    <div class="sec-title">When This Technique BREAKS</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Non-adjacent / non-contiguous requirement</strong> — "No two adjacent elements" (House Robber) changes the recurrence to dp[i] = max(dp[i−1], dp[i−2] + nums[i]); Kadane's "extend or restart" is invalid.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Exact sum required</strong> — "Find subarray with sum = k" with negatives: Kadane's shrink logic breaks. Use prefix sum + HashMap.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Count of all subarrays satisfying a condition</strong> — Kadane's finds one optimal subarray; counting all requires prefix map or at-most decomposition.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Maximum subarray of exact fixed length</strong> — Use a fixed sliding window of size k; Kadane's variable-length nature doesn't apply.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Empty subarray allowed when all values are negative</strong> — If empty subarray is permitted the answer is 0; standard Kadane's (init to nums[0]) returns negative. Clarify the empty-subarray contract.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Product with zeros</strong> — Max product subarray needs special handling: zeros reset both maxProd and minProd. Failing to handle zeros gives incorrect results.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>2D problem without column-compression</strong> — Running Kadane's row-by-row misses cross-row rectangles. Fix column boundaries → compress rows → apply 1D Kadane's.</div>

                    <div class="sec-title">3-Phase Mastery Plan</div>
                    <div class="info-box">
                        <strong>Phase 1 — Solve (in order):</strong> #1 → #2 → #3 → #4 → #5 → #9 → #10 → #6 → #7 → #14 → #12 → #18 → #20 → #21 → #11 → #13<br>
                        Problems 1–3 nail the three canonical forms (sum, product, circular). Problems 4–5 expand the state space. Custom #9–#10 force first-principles derivation, not memorisation. #18 (tree path sum) appears directly in Google interviews. #20 (largest variance) is the hardest recognition problem; do it after all Medium variants. #11 closes the 2D chapter.<br><br>
                        <strong>Phase 2 — Drill:</strong> Before coding each problem, explicitly write the Kadane's state variables: "What does maxEndingHere mean here? When do I reset? When do I update global?" Practise the 1D→2D transition: given any 2D sum problem, immediately compress to 1D using fixed column boundaries — this should become automatic. Always init to nums[0], never 0, unless empty subarray is explicitly allowed.<br><br>
                        <strong>Phase 3 — Validate:</strong> AtCoder ABC/ARC — search "maximum subarray" (several problems disguise Kadane's in scoring games). USACO Silver "Hoof, Paper, Scissors" — multi-state transitions extending Kadane's DP. HackerRank DP set: "Max Array Sum" and "The Maximum Subarray" test all-negative and non-adjacent variants back-to-back.
                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">80% Coverage Set</div>
                    <div class="coverage-box"><strong>Minimum 10 problems:</strong> <span class="pill">LC 53</span><span class="pill">LC 152</span><span class="pill">LC 918</span><span class="pill">LC 1749</span><span class="pill">LC 1186</span><span class="pill">Custom #10</span><span class="pill">LC 1074</span><span class="pill">LC 1031</span><span class="pill">LC 124</span><span class="pill">LC 2272</span></div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Red Flags</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Initialising maxSoFar = 0 instead of nums[0]</strong> — Returns 0 for all-negative arrays, implying the empty subarray was chosen. Always init both variables to nums[0] and start the loop at index 1.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Not tracking both maxProd AND minProd in the product variant</strong> — Negative × negative = large positive; tracking only maxProd loses this when a second negative appears. Swap both on every negative element.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Circular array: not handling the all-negative edge case</strong> — totalSum − minSubarraySum = 0 (empty array) when all elements are negative, which is invalid. If maxNormal &lt; 0, return maxNormal directly.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Tree path sum: returning both branches to the parent</strong> — leftGain + rightGain + node.val is the global candidate, but you can only return max(leftGain, rightGain) + node.val upward. Returning both breaks parent path continuity.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Deletion variant: wrong initialisation of withDeletion[0]</strong> — withDeletion[0] should be 0 (delete first element) or −∞ depending on empty-subarray policy; wrong init cascades through the entire DP.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Treating "at most one deletion" as a sliding window</strong> — The two-state DP (withDelete, withoutDelete) is correct; a sliding window doesn't generalise when the deletion can be anywhere.</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Missing max(0, gain) in the tree variant</strong> — Always take max(0, childGain) when propagating from children. Forgetting this includes loss-making subtrees in the path sum.</div>
                </div></div>
